1. angular directive- to manipulate dom
1.1 component directive
1.2 structural directive- to add or remove html elements based on some condition/length
                          of an array
1.2.1 *ngIf="condition"   
1.2.2 *ngFor="let variable name of array-name"                       

2. activateroute is a class name and it s used to take a particular details from an api
the class params is used for that

3.data binding
oneway binding
--------------
3.1 component(ts) to view(html)
      3.1.1 string interpolation  syntax: {{event-property-name}} in html
      3.1.2 property binding syntax: [attribute]="event-property-name"
3.2 view(html) to component(ts)    
      3.2.1 event binding - (event-name)="function call()"  
      3.2.2 event binding using $event -  (event-name)="function call($event)"

two way binding
---------------
3.3 ngModel- [()]     

